title: For Sale:  Ruger 10/22, M1 Carbine conversion, includes 850 rounds of 22 LR ammo!
postcontent:
This rifle started life as a standard 10/22 carbine and was stripped down to nothing but the receiver, bolt and barrel. I gave the bolt a light bluing and the receiver has been painted a dull gray to match the original rifle. I took an EA Brown Co Beech M1 carbine style stock ($110), stripped the nasty red stain they used and applied a hand rubbed walnut oil stain. The sights have been upgraded with an M1 carbine style front + rear set from Centerfire Systems ($80), and the drift-only rear sight further upgraded with a reproduction M1 carbine adjustable sight ($50).  The non-adjustable (early style) rear sight is included along with the adjustable sight that is installed. I've added a reproduction oiler, sling and dual magazine pouch ($40 for the set) in desert tan as well as an extended charging handle ($30) to complete the look and feel. It's also had a Hornet Spitfire drop-in trigger unit installed which gets you the extended mag release, auto bolt release and a 2.5 pound release. ($120). I'm also including 2 x 10 round Ruger 10/22 magazines, one of which is glued to the bottom portion of a Korean import M1 carbine magazine. Another pre-cut magazine body plus a complete M1 carbine 20 round magazine is also included. 

This rifle is fully compatible with all standard Ruger 10/22 magazines including the 10, 15 and 25 round BX series magazines.

** Note that the rifle package also includes TWO full/sealed cartons of Federal AutoMatch .22 LR ammo (650 rounds) plus a partial carton that contains 200 rounds for a total of 850 rounds.**

P2P/P2C and an MN drivers license along with a signed bill of sale are required.

title: For Sale:  sig sauer p250 compact 9mm
postcontent:
tritium night sights
Only had 30 rounds through it 
3x 15 round magazine

I believe it is a crimson trace red sight
Original box and papers
Weight	
720 g (25.4 oz) P250 Compact (incl magazine)
Length
183 mm (7.2 in) P250 Compact
Features	
A key feature of the pistol is its modular design. The main module of the P250 is an internal stainless steel frame fire control unit which consist of the integrated fire control group (trigger, hammer and all necessary linkage and springs), ambidextrous slide release (one on each side of the pistol), ejector and four slide rails. This steel receiver unit is used in every P250 grip module, top end, and chambering combination and is inserted into the grip frame module and held in place by the axis pin of the disassembly lever. The firearm's serial number is on the fire control unit instead of the grip module. The fire control unit allows the operator to interchange differently-sized slide assembly or top end modules and polymer grip frame modules and trigger shoes and (limited) chambering conversions to adapt the gun to the individual user and address different needs.

The P250 was designed to be ambidextrous in handling, sporting an ambidextrous slide catch lever and user reversible magazine catch. All other operating controls are designed so they can be operated from either side. The firearm can be field stripped with no tools.

The full-size and compact grip modules feature an integral Picatinny rail mounting-bracket at the lower forward edge of the module to allow the mounting of laser sights, tactical lights, and other accessories. Before the introduction of the Picatinny rail SIG used a differing Rail Integration System on the P250 Compact.

Pistola Lancia-Razzi Mod.1900 6mm Cal / 22 Nera MMM Mondial Made in Italy

Lancia-Razzi Model 1900 6mm 22 cal Pistol
Brevettata, EIG, Made in Italy
Tear Gas / Starter Pistol 
1940’s – 1950’s Production
Works Flawlessly with No Mechanical Issues

Comes as shown with Original box, Removable 6 Shot Slide in Clip for loading in front of gun, Original Instructions 
There is a small pin that swings out from the bottom of the grip, it’s about 1/2" long for pushing shells out  
Inside the box it says that this pistol works with cal 22 Crimped Blank Flobert Ballets 

Back in the 1950's they were $13.07 New by mail order from
UNITED SAFETY SUPPLY Cherokee Institute 310 West 9th St. Kansas City Missouri 64105

At one time I had some blanks for this and it worked well, however I do not have them anymore so it comes without any “ammo”
Blanks are available through a number of places on the internet, not sure locally I just haven’t looked.
Tear Gas loads I have seen on occasion but they are difficult to find most of the time. This would be neat but I have never shot any of the tear gas rounds.
These DO NOT Shoot Regular Bullets and as far as I know they Cannot be modified to shoot standard bullets.
The Barrel is NOT plugged as a few sites say, possibly the newer ones are, but not this old of a model. The charge (gas) is pushed up into the barrel and then out. Barrel has extreme rifling that appears good, perhaps this is to disperse the gas out the barrel in a wider pattern. But this is merely conjecture on my part, not having seen or shot a tear gas round through it.

A Very Nice Collectable that could be used if you wanted and one that is not an easy one to find complete with box and instructions.

$100.00
Email me with any questions or for additional pictures
I will meet ½ way depending on location
Thank you
